# Wedora Vendor Marketplace — Implementation Plan v2

## Executive Summary

Build a three-sided Vendor Marketplace ecosystem within the existing Wedora platform:
- **Couples** discover, filter, and shortlist vendors from a public directory
- **Vendors** register, manage their business profiles, portfolios, and subscription plans
- **Admins** moderate listings, manage subscriptions, and control featured placements

The marketplace will be the **primary organic traffic engine** for Wedora — every vendor profile is a fully SEO-optimized, publicly crawlable page with structured data.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Critical Architectural Decision:** The existing `vendors` table (scoped to `wedding_id`) is the **private Vendor Tracker** — a couple's personal vendor management tool. The marketplace requires a **completely separate schema** (`marketplace_vendors`, `vendor_listings`, etc.) that represents real businesses. When a couple shortlists a marketplace vendor, we create a bridge record linking the two systems. This keeps the existing Vendor Tracker fully intact and backward-compatible.

> [!WARNING]
> **Supabase Storage Required:** Vendor portfolios need image/video uploads. This plan assumes Supabase Storage is enabled on your project. If not, we'll need to configure a storage bucket (`vendor-media`) with appropriate policies.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Vendor Auth Model:** Vendors will register using the same Supabase auth system but with a `role: 'vendor'` in `user_metadata`. This means a single person can be both a couple-user AND a vendor (different contexts, same login). Please confirm this is acceptable vs. requiring separate accounts.

