## Navigation Architecture (Redesigned)

This is the core UX redesign. The current sidebar has a **flat list of 10+ items** which would become unmanageable with marketplace additions. The new design uses **three distinct layout contexts** with clean, grouped navigation.

### The Problem (Current State)
```
Current Sidebar (flat, 12+ items):
├── Dashboard
├── Invitations
├── WhatsApp Tools
├── Budget
├── Guests
├── Tasks
├── Timeline
├── Vendors (Tracker)
├── Inspiration
├── Blog
├── [Admin Dashboard]      ← admin only
├── [Admin Blog]           ← admin only
├── Settings
└── User / Logout
```
Adding marketplace (3+ items), vendor dashboard (5+ items), and admin controls (2+ items) would create a **20+ item sidebar** — terrible UX.

### The Solution: Three Layout Contexts

```mermaid
